  Things get complicated if the code has more than 2 digits, but keep in mind
that few people use the remote access feature, and many don't even know what
it is!  So... no one gets hot if the code has been changed (you can't change
it on some).  Always try the defaults first:

 1111,0000,1234,9999 and such.

 Some of the the newer models have an interesting feature: when a message is
left, it will call a preset number and forward the message.  This type of
machine has 4 or 5 digit codes, but if we can crack it we can set it to make
international calls.  It would be even better if we could be there when the
guy gets his phone bill!

